---
// "Data" page: a per-theme directory of source agencies, plus how to report an
// error. Deliberately no pipeline mechanics or cadence tables — freshness is
// stamped on the content itself ("data through {month}"). New themes append a
// section here as they land. Linked from Footer.
import StoryPage from '../layouts/StoryPage.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../components/editorial/SectionHeader.astro';

const themes = [
  {
    label: 'Economy',
    agencies: [
      {
        name: 'Reserve Bank of India (RBI)',
        href: 'https://www.rbi.org.in/',
        role: 'Settlement and payment-system statistics: UPI, NEFT, RTGS, cards and settlement systems, published as monthly Excel releases.',
      },
      {
        name: 'National Payments Corporation of India (NPCI)',
        href: 'https://www.npci.org.in/',
        role: 'Product-level statistics for the rails NPCI operates: UPI and IMPS broken down by bank, app, state and merchant category.',
      },
    ],
  },
];
---

<StoryPage
  title="Data — Time Series of India"
  description="Where TSOI's data comes from: the official source agencies behind each theme, and how to report an error."
>
  <SectionHeader label="Data" />
  <article class="prose">
    <p>
      Every series on TSOI is built from an official statistical release, and every read and
      dashboard shows how recent its data is. The sources, by theme:
    </p>
    {
      themes.map((t) => (
        <>
          <h3>{t.label}</h3>
          <ul>
            {t.agencies.map((a) => (
              <li>
                <a
                  href={a.href}
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  aria-label={`Open the ${a.name} homepage (opens in new tab)`}
                >
                  {a.name}
                </a>
                — {a.role}
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </>
      ))
    }
    <p class="future">More themes — and their sources — will be listed here as they launch.</p>

    <h3>How the data is handled</h3>
    <p>
      Figures come from the releases as published, with a small amount of preparation before
      charting: units are converted for display (millions become crore), product variants that a
      source lists separately are combined when they are one instrument, and names that drift
      across the source's own files, a bank capitalised three ways or a merchant category renamed
      midway through a year, are unified under a single label. Merchant categories are keyed by
      NPCI's own MCC code for exactly this reason. The values themselves are never changed; where
      a chart and the official release disagree, the release is right and we want to know.
    </p>

    <h3>Spotted an error?</h3>
    <p>
      If a chart disagrees with the official release, please
      <a href="https://github.com/time-series-of-india/tsoi/issues">open an issue on GitHub</a>
      with a link to the page and the release you checked against. Corrections ship with the next
      rebuild.
    </p>

    <h3>Reuse &amp; disclaimer</h3>
    <p>
      Data is © its publishing agency (currently the Reserve Bank of India and NPCI); TSOI
      claims no ownership over it and attributes every figure to its source. Where our figures
      and a source disagree, the source is correct. Map boundaries are illustrative only and are not an authority on any boundary;
      refer to the Survey of India. You're welcome to cite TSOI's charts and writing with
      attribution and a link. For reuse of the underlying statistics beyond informational,
      non-commercial purposes, check the source agency's own terms.
    </p>
    <p>
      Time Series of India is provided for informational and educational purposes only. It is
      independent and <strong>not affiliated with, endorsed by, or representing</strong> the
      Reserve Bank of India, the National Payments Corporation of India, or the Government of
      India. It has no connection with The Times of India or any other news publication; the
      name refers to time series, the statistical kind.
      Figures may differ from the primary source; verify against the original before
      relying on them. The site is provided “as is,” without warranties of any kind, and its
      maintainers accept no liability for decisions made on the basis of it. Trademarks (UPI,
      IMPS, RuPay, and bank or app names) belong to their respective owners and are used only to
      identify the services they name.
    </p>
  </article>
</StoryPage>

<style>
  .prose {
    max-width: 70ch;
    margin-top: calc(var(--tsoi-spacing-unit) * 2);
  }

  .prose h3 {
    margin: calc(var(--tsoi-spacing-unit) * 3) 0 0;
    font: var(--tsoi-text-headline-md);
    letter-spacing: var(--tsoi-text-headline-md-tracking);
  }

  .prose p,
  .prose ul {
    margin: var(--tsoi-spacing-unit) 0 0;
    font: var(--tsoi-text-deck);
    letter-spacing: var(--tsoi-text-deck-tracking);
  }

  .prose ul {
    padding-left: 1.3em;
  }

  .prose li {
    margin-top: var(--tsoi-spacing-unit);
  }

  .prose a {
    color: var(--tsoi-color-primary-text);
  }

  .future {
    color: var(--tsoi-color-on-surface-variant);
  }
</style>
